<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1738,1913]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,285,1738,1764]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1969" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1969" box="[593,932,1738,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Afrascius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,709,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Afrascius</emphasis>
Linnavuori, 
<quantity box="[871,932,1738,1764]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.00126" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="in" value="1969.0">1969</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having a Y-shaped connective, paired aedeagal shafts and a subapical process on each shaft, but can be distinguished by the subgenital plates having a caudal attenuated process, and the aedeagus without long ventral appendages and with the gonopores subapical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
